issue_comment_body:
@dabeaz , I also like the idea of a "trash queue" for tasks. 

As for the task tree, this might also be useful for the "monitor" feature. I can imagine a case, when some evil task spawns a lot of new tasks, that will DOS the event loop in some way. Obviously, if you use curio monitor to manually kill all those tasks, you'll be out of luck, since cancelling say 100 child tasks is already hard, while this could be done pretty smart if we implement a "group cancellation" on top of this PR. But again, I'm just theory crafting. I would also prefer to keep curio as simple and robust as possible, though I don't know whether this particular patch is harmful. Let's see what the community thinks.

>  if a parent task exits, then the corresponding Task object won't be cleaned up until all of its children have exited?

@njsmith , actually, when a parent is cleaned up, all it's child will have a main task as their new parent, just like in unix all child processes become child of init process when a parent exits.

