Now ... in doing this, I discovered a bug. Notice how the decorators are implemented here.

```
@app.route("/protected_user")
@inject_user()
@protected
async def my_protected_user(request, user):
```

They will work in this configuration, but it is a bug. Adding `@protected()` will result in:

    TypeError: decorated_function() missing 1 required positional argument: 'request'

I will work on fixing this.

Also, I just realized that you cannot `from sanic_jwt import inject_user`, but have to grab it from `from sanic_jwt.decorators import inject_user`.

Another bug worth correcting.

